    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense, but it sounds pretty heavy. It phrased it as \"any and all losses\" and mentioned \"third-party claims.\" Does that mean if someone else sues the client because of something I did, I'm the one who has to pay for their lawyers too? It feels like there might be some hidden risks buried in that wording.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're right to be cautious; that wording does indeed cover a broad range of potential issues, including third-party claims. In other words, if someone outside of the Client and you, the Consultant, sues because of your actions or statements, you would be responsible for covering their legal fees as well as any other related costs. It's a bit like saying, \"If my mistake causes trouble for someone else, I'll be the one to clean up the mess, no matter who else gets involved.\" It's important to carefully review this clause and possibly consult with a legal professional to fully understand the extent of your responsibilities and to ensure you're comfortable with the risks involved.",
